# Notebook / quickstart runtime artifacts.
#
# The example notebooks under notebooks/ (and the `forgelm quickstart`
# walkthroughs) write their generated config, dataset, checkpoint and export
# artifacts into the CURRENT WORKING DIRECTORY — i.e. the repo root when a
# contributor runs them in-place. None of it is source: it is regenerated by
# re-running the cell. Without these rules a `git add -A` after running a
# notebook silently commits a demo config (or a multi-GB checkpoint) — which is
# exactly how `safety_config.yaml` slipped into the tree once.
#
# Root-anchored on purpose: `/audit/` must not shadow a future
# `docs/**/audit/`, and `*_config.yaml` must never touch `config_template.yaml`
# (the canonical, CI-validated example) — it does not match, but anchoring
# keeps that guarantee local to the repo root.
/*_config.yaml
/my_config.yaml
/*_checkpoints/
/audit/
/audit_minhash/
/audit_quality/
/curated/
/safety_results.json
/safety_trend.jsonl
/kto_data.jsonl
/math_prompts.jsonl
/teacher_responses.jsonl
/Modelfile
/vllm.yaml
/endpoint.json
/*.gguf
